<div class="insights-card">
  <h2>&#128203; Key Insights</h2>
  <div class="insight-item">
    <div class="insight-icon icon-green">&#128200;</div>
    <div class="insight-content">
      <h4>Combined at-risk down to 23.1% — strongest result across all three cycles</h4>
      <p>Confirmed churn held steady at 12.6% (vs 12.4% in June 1&#8211;12) while unclear calls dropped sharply to 10.5% from 17.3%. Combined at-risk is now 23.1%, down from 29.6% last cycle and 36% in May. A meaningful positive trend across the month of June.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="insight-item">
    <div class="insight-icon icon-amber">&#129309;</div>
    <div class="insight-content">
      <h4>Retention success improved but attempt rate dropped</h4>
      <p>When reps did attempt retention, success rate climbed to 26.8% (up from 20%). However, retention was only attempted on 14.8% of calls, down from 22.1% last cycle. Reps are getting better at retaining when they try, but are attempting less frequently overall.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="insight-item">
    <div class="insight-icon icon-red">&#128184;</div>
    <div class="insight-content">
      <h4>Pricing and lead ROI remain the top two churn drivers for the third consecutive cycle</h4>
      <p>Pricing/cost (30%) and low ROI on leads (25%) account for 55% of at-risk churn reasons, consistent across May, June 1&#8211;12, and June 15&#8211;30. Product dissatisfaction has grown to 22%, up from 13% in June 1&#8211;12, and is now a close third.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="insight-item">
    <div class="insight-icon icon-red">&#128267;</div>
    <div class="insight-content">
      <h4>mdelacruz and jmesina are recurring coaching flags across both June cycles</h4>
      <p>mdelacruz appeared in both June 1&#8211;12 and June 15&#8211;30 with high at-risk rates and below-average retention attempt rates. jmesina's retention attempt rate dropped to 6.7% this cycle despite 26.7% at-risk exposure. Both are high-priority for targeted coaching.</p>
    </div>
